text: Worth County is a county in the U.S. state of Iowa. As of the 2020 census, the population was 7,443. The county seat is Northwood. The county was founded in 1851 and named for Major General William Jenkins Worth (1794–1849), an officer in both the Seminole War and the Mexican–American War. == References == Category:1851 establishments in Iowa Category:Iowa counties
title: Worth County, Iowa
